claim: Vaccination with a higher-dose recombinant flu vaccine may induce a more robust antibody response than egg-based standard-dose vaccines.
explanation: Header of a CDC Morbidity and Mortality Weekly Report (MMWR) Recommendations and Reports, Volume 71, Number 1, dated August 26, 20XX, with MMWR logo and document title does not support the claim because the image contains only the title header of the report and no data or statements about antibody responses to higher-dose recombinant versus egg-based standard-dose flu vaccines Note: The image is limited to the publication header and contains no study figures or data; thus, absence of relevant evidence is expected
